    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sh-Oligopeptide-1 sr-Egyptian Scorpion Oligopeptide-1 is a single chain fusion peptide, produced by fermentation in  E. coli. The starting gene is synthesized by the fusion of the gene from sh-Oligopeptide-1 and sr-Egyptian Scorpion Oligopeptide-1. The fusion peptide contains 90 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
